                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-sergeant B</hi> 14.) On the afternoon of the 22nd of October I saw the prisoner leave the back of the house, No. 10, Bel grave-square, where there were some repairs doing—I followed, and stopped him in Knightsbridge, and asked what he had got—he said, "Nothing"—I found one piece of lead in his trowsers, and three other pieces in his waistcoat and jacket pockets.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
